</taxonomicName>
subgroup of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1812" box="[1046,1147,1055,1081]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="histrio">
<emphasis box="[1046,1147,1055,1081]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">P. histrio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[1234,1429,1055,1081]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">Shinohara 2002b</bibRefCitation>
) and is most closely related to the European 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dahlbom, 1835)" baseAuthorityName="Dahlbom" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[640,983,1090,1117]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gyllenhali">
<emphasis box="[640,780,1091,1117]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">P. gyllenhali</emphasis>
(Dahlbom, 1835)
</taxonomicName>
. These two allopatric species are similar morphologically, though distinguishable from each other, and share the same host plant and larval habits (Shinohara 1995; 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Hara, H." box="[224,501,1163,1189]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" pagination="295 - 297" refId="ref77816" refString="Shinohara, A. &amp; Hara, H. (2009) Discovery of host plant and larva of Pamphilius tricolor (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae) in Hokkaido, Japan. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology, 15, 295 - 297." type="journal article" year="2009">Shinohara &amp; Hara 2009</bibRefCitation>
). The available COI data for the two species were retrieved as monophyletic with 100% UFBoot support, but the two species were not clearly differentiated within the clade (
<figureCitation box="[1178,1277,1199,1225]" captionStart="FIGURES 142–143" captionStartId="230.[151,264,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[157,1426,182,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-26@230.[151,1436,181,1887]" captionTargetPageId="230" captionText="FIGURES 142–143. Condensed ML tree based on CO1 gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius 142. histrio group. 143. inanitus group." pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 142</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
